text.__SUMMARY__: Eucalyptus risdonii is a rare species of Eucalypt, endemic to southern Tasmania. E. risdonii was first described by Joseph Dalton Hooker in 1847. Its common names include Risdon peppermint. It is reported as being a juvenilised form of its sister species, E. tenuiramisE. risdonii is the floral emblem of Geilston Bay High School
